Most discoveries don’t come from polished papers.

They come from messy notebooks full of:
	•	sketches
	•	partial equations
	•	wrong attempts
	•	small insights

Traditional notebooks capture the result, but not the thinking process.

A thinking canvas records the whole chain:

idea
 ↓
experiment
 ↓
mistake
 ↓
refinement
 ↓
result

